t get the fight under control PDQ, you don't stand a chance.<P>A lot of clerics pre-res prefer to sacrifice themselves.  In higher level hunts, it is not practical.  In most situations, it would take longer to have the cleric rezzed than for the cleric to survive and res everyone after.<P><P>------------------<BR>Hinanar Goodhammer<BR>Vicar of Brell Seliris<BR>Cazic-Thule Server<BR>Guild of Albion "Death before Dishonour!"<P>'Clerics can tank...we're just no good at dealing damage'</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nizdaar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Do that many of you actually keep gate up?  I haven't had it loaded in a group situation since around level 27, when I started grouping with evacers.<P>------------------<BR>Nizdaar<BR>56 High-Elf Cleric<BR>Innoruuk Server<BR> <A HREF="http://www.maximumeq.com" TARGET=_blank>http://www.maximumeq.com</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cland</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I looked at the Reso/Symbol line but they wouldn't work either  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"> went back to daring, and nothing has this kind of healing power.<P>But if I was in this kind of situation I would step up into the melee and take a *few* hits and start chain casting Sup heal on him<P><BR>Cland Carbuncle<BR>Lvl 51 Vicar, Rallos Zek<BR>Court Of the Crosswinds</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Trilvan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aean- The problem with your situation is if you have to cast comp heal before the fight then have the tank engage because he would die before comp heal would go off then once the tank did taunt the mob off you he would be doomed to die before you could heal him again. <BR>A mob that is going to be hiting that hard is going to have several thousand hps and will take more than one comp heal on the tank to deal out that much damage. However your idea does have merit in a multiple cleric situation. Say 3 clerics rotating the agro with comp heals and using da and db to survive the onslaught with the tank not taunting. the timing would be incredibly tricky since the tank would have to take some damage for the agro to shift between clerics healing the tank.<BR>Actualy an intresting idea but would have to be in a complete trust group with some incredible timing between clerics and tank.<P>As for the original idea lets do this. Lets say you are fighting mobs that are Quading for 300 with a thank that has 3500 hps in a group war, cleric, Echanter, wizard, backup warrior. Primary warrior is only one taunting. cleric is below level 49. I think those numbers are little closer to reality how would you handle this what heals when.<P>------------------<BR>Trilvan Lostheart<BR>46th Cleric of Love Peace and Happiness<BR>Markham Rosrac<BR>52nd Modrod handin, coldstone passin, pet a bashin, Gician</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shohanna Curesurtales</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My only beef with the senario is the fact that a 44 cleric healing a 2k+ warrior is around lvl 45 or so.. And your not going to engage 1 mob for 300d/s,  Even Vox and Naggie don't hit 1 time for that much.  So the situation is impossible. <P>Unless it is multiple mobs.<P>And even if it's multiple mobs,  you will have a fairly balanced group or you wouldn't be in the area of (these mobs)..  <P>And once YOU the cleric, buff the tank.. He IS going to have more then 25k Hp.. around there anyway.. The numbers just don't match up.. <P>I am just starting to use CH, and if my tank was going down that fast, I cast SH and call evac anyway..  But you need more information to actually see the situation. I see the suggestions that were made here.  Most of them are assuming this or that.  But I would li